By-the-way, this idiom ought to work somewhat better (for analysis purposes):
```
if m < 0 {
  return
} // this might be necessary; easier analysis should suffice if m>=0 is known.
n := len(a)/m
// m*n <= len(a), no overflow possible.
for i := 0: i < m; i++ {
    for j := 0 ; j <n ;j++{
       _ =  a[i*m + j]
   }
}
```
